{"items":[{"category":"Provisioning","homepage_url":"https://www.kubewarden.io","id":"provisioning--security-compliance--kubewarden","logo":"logos/24207e926905a8f8a35dce3be43c4da4f8d9e8edea46b2beb3c319d6857b8e7a.svg","name":"Kubewarden","subcategory":"Security & Compliance","website":"https://www.kubewarden.io","accepted_at":"2022-06-17","additional_categories":[{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/tree/master/projects/kubewarden","blog_url":"https://kubewarden.io/blog","chat_channel":"#kubewarden","clomonitor_name":"kubewarden","clomonitor_report_summary":"images/clomonitor_cncf_kubewarden.svg","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","description":"Kubewarden is a Policy Engine powered by WebAssembly policies. Its policies can be written in CEL, Rego (OPA & Gatekeeper flavours), Rust, Go, YAML, and others. Kubewarden simplifies Policy-As-Code by allowing policy authors and consumers to use their preferred tooling and stack, develop and test policies out of cluster. ","devstats_url":"https://kubewarden.devstats.cncf.io/","documentation_url":"https://docs.kubewarden.io","github_discussions_url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/community/discussions","lfx_slug":"kubewarden","mailing_list_url":"https://lists.cncf.io/g/cncf-kubewarden-maintainers","maturity":"sandbox","package_manager_url":"https://artifacthub.io/packages/search?kind=0&kind=13&ts_query_web=kubewarden&official=true&sort=relevance","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/kubewarden-controller","primary":true},{"url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/policy-server","primary":false},{"url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/kwctl","primary":false},{"url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/audit-scanner","primary":false},{"url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/community","primary":false}],"slack_url":"https://kubernetes.slack.com/","summary":{"business_use_case":"Embracing WebAssembly for policies means that Policy Authors can use their preferred tooling (language libraries, Git, CI); thus lowering knowledge barrier and silos, reducing training, and minimizing ad-hoc solutions. Thanks to policies being WebAssembly, Kubewarden policies can leverage and reuse upstream libraries to expand on current policy solutions while keeping compatibility (e.g: its cel-policy uses Kubernetes' cel-go interpreter, its kyverno-policy compiles a subset of Kyverno codebase to support Kyverno's YAML-like DSL).  Kubewarden policy CRDs and PolicyServer CRD enable insulation of consumers per namespace, and self-service.","integrations":"Sigstore, Cosign, OpenTelemetry, Prometheus, Grafana, Jaeger, Policy Reporter","intro_url":"https://docs.kubewarden.io/quick-start","personas":["Platform engineering","DevOps engineers","Security admins","Cluster admins","Policy authors"],"release_rate":"Approximately monthly for minor releases, when needed for patch releases.","tags":["wasm","webassembly","web assembly","policy","policy-as-code","governance","software supply chain","pod security","compliance"],"use_case":"Kubewarden is a Policy Engine powered by WebAssembly policies. Its policies can be written in CEL, Rego (OPA & Gatekeeper flavours), Rust, Go, YAML, and others. Kubewarden simplifies Policy-As-Code by allowing policy authors and consumers to use their preferred tooling and stack, develop and test policies out of cluster. "},"tag":["security"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/kubewarden"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://knative.dev","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--knative","logo":"logos/6a1b7572490f95cada1836b3e0f932e5ff10c683bc1167b08ff868fb7867cfd5.svg","name":"Knative","subcategory":"Scheduling & Orchestration","website":"https://knative.dev","accepted_at":"2022-03-02","additional_categories":[{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Installable Platform"},{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"},{"category":"AI Native Infra","subcategory":"Orchestration and Scheduling"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/tree/main/docs/images/logo","audits":[{"date":"2023-07-13","type":"fuzzing","url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/tree/main/reports/ADA-knative-fuzzing-audit-22-23.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"},{"date":"2023-11-27","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/knative/docs/blob/main/reports/ADA-knative-security-audit-2023.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"}],"clomonitor_name":"knative","clomonitor_report_summary":"images/clomonitor_cncf_knative.svg","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","description":"Knative is a developer-focused serverless application layer which is a great complement to the existing Kubernetes application constructs. Knative consists of three components: an HTTP-triggered autoscaling container runtime called “Knative Serving”, a CloudEvents-over-HTTP asynchronous routing layer called “Knative Eventing”, and a developer-focused function framework which leverages the Serving and Eventing components, called \"Knative Functions\".","devstats_url":"https://knative.devstats.cncf.io/","featured":{"label":"CNCF Graduated","order":1},"graduated_at":"2025-09-11","incubating_at":"2022-03-02","lfx_slug":"knative","mailing_list_url":"https://groups.google.com/d/forum/knative-users","maturity":"graduated","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/knative/serving","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://slack.cncf.io","stack_overflow_url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/knative","summary":{"business_use_case":"The power of Knative’s eventing and serverless features allows companies to bridge processes between external eventing systems with services and functions in Kubernetes.","integrations":"Apache Kafka, RabbitMQ, Redis, CNCF Buildpacks, Docker, Podman","intro_url":"https://knative.dev/docs/getting-started/","personas":["Cloud Architects","Cloud Developers","Platform Engineers","DevOps Engineers","DevOps Practitioners"],"release_rate":"Quarterly major releases","tags":["Serverless","CloudEvents","Functions","Scaling","Applications"],"use_case":"Knative is system that helps teams develop, build, manage, and maintain processes in Kubernetes. Its purpose is to simplify, automate, and monitor deployments of Kubernetes so teams spend less time on maintenance and more time on app development and projects. Knative takes over repetitive and time-intensive tasks while removing obstacles and delays."},"tag":["runtime"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/KnativeProject","youtube_url":"https://www.youtube.com/c/KnativeProject"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://openfunction.dev","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--openfunction","logo":"logos/eec49b43a5d92bd4b19cbad9a4007e88d16c46f1b15d6d47ff4800c6dce36076.svg","name":"OpenFunction","subcategory":"Scheduling & Orchestration","website":"https://openfunction.dev","accepted_at":"2022-04-26","additional_categories":[{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Installable Platforms"},{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/tree/master/projects/openfunction","blog_url":"https://openfunction.dev/blog/","chat_channel":"#openfunction","clomonitor_name":"openfunction","clomonitor_report_summary":"images/clomonitor_cncf_openfunction.svg","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","devstats_url":"https://openfunction.devstats.cncf.io/","lfx_slug":"openfunction","maturity":"sandbox","latest_annual_review_at":"2023-06-23","latest_annual_review_url":"https://github.com/cncf/toc/pull/1097","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/OpenFunction/OpenFunction","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://slack.cncf.io/","summary":{"business_use_case":"OpenFunction is a cloud-native open source FaaS (Function as a Service) platform aiming to let users focus on their business logic without having to  maintain the underlying runtime environment and infrastructure. Users can generate event-driven and dynamically scaling Serverless workloads by simply  submitting business-related source code in the form of functions. Users can also build and run serverless applications as well.","integration":"Knative, Dapr, KEDA, Shipwright, Kubernetes Gateway API, Contour","intro_url":"https://openfunction.dev/docs/","personas":["Developers","Platform engineers"],"release_rate":"3 ~ 4 major releases per year","tags":["FaaS","Serverless","KEDA","Knative","Shipwright","Buildpacks","Distributed Systems"],"use_case":"Users can use OpenFunction in several different ways including building functions or applications only, running sync or async serverless functions or applications, building and then running serverless functions or applications, building and then running serverless wasm applications(In progress).  In all use cases, users can utilize Dapr to communicate with various backend services (BaaS)."},"tag":["runtime"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/openfunctiondev"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","homepage_url":"https://dapr.io","id":"app-definition-and-development--application-definition-image-build--dapr","logo":"logos/5b3a3f211aae4c129ca1aa9bf3cf52cf12fc7fe5a3c6bc44744ca45ccd697597.svg","name":"Dapr","subcategory":"Application Definition & Image Build","website":"https://dapr.io","accepted_at":"2021-11-09","additional_categories":[{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"},{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Framework"}],"artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/blob/master/examples/graduated.md#dapr-logos","audits":[{"date":"2023-06-30","type":"fuzzing","url":"https://docs.dapr.io/docs/Dapr-june-2023-fuzzing-audit-report.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"},{"date":"2023-09-05","type":"security","url":"https://docs.dapr.io/docs/Dapr-september-2023-security-audit-report.pdf","vendor":"Ada Logics"}],"blog_url":"https://blog.dapr.io/posts","clomonitor_name":"dapr","clomonitor_report_summary":"images/clomonitor_cncf_dapr.svg","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","devstats_url":"https://dapr.devstats.cncf.io/","featured":{"label":"CNCF Graduated","order":1},"graduated_at":"2024-10-30","incubating_at":"2021-11-09","lfx_slug":"dapr","maturity":"graduated","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/dapr/dapr","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://discord.com/invite/ptHhX6jc34","summary":{"business_use_case":"Deliver distributed system applications in half the time. Dapr provides APIs that abstract away the complexity of common challenges developers encounter regularly when building distributed applications. These API building blocks can be leveraged as the need arises - use one, several, or all to develop applications faster and deliver solutions on time. Dapr leverages proven practices for distributed application development that enable developers to build resilient, secured systems. By using Dapr in your application, you adopt these best practices without having to spend time solving common challenges.","integration":"Kubernetes, Docker, Open Telemetry, gRPC, CloudEvents, spiffe, Knative, Helm, Prometheus, Cert Manager","intro_url":"https://youtu.be/9o9iDAgYBA8","personas":["Developers","Platform engineers"],"release_rate":"4 times per year (each quarter)","tags":["Developer APIs","Distributed Systems","Microservices","HTTP","gRPC","Go","Java","Python",".NET","Javascript","C++","Rust","CLI"],"use_case":"The Distributed Application Runtime (Dapr) provides APIs that simplify microservice architecture development and increases developer productivity. Whether your communication pattern is service-to-service invocation or pub/sub messaging, Dapr helps you write resilient and secured microservices. By letting Dapr’s sidecar take care of the complex challenges such as service discovery, message broker integration, encryption, observability, and secret management, developers can focus on business logic and keep their code simple."},"tag":["app-delivery"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/DaprDev"},{"category":"Wasm","homepage_url":"https://ekuiper.org","id":"wasm--embedded-functions--ekuiper","logo":"logos/8e241f1145fcf8ca479d6a65e04a1ef7e5ca9817e2d25dfe08953b649b22fb20.svg","name":"eKuiper","subcategory":"Embedded Functions","website":"https://ekuiper.org","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/linux-foundation-edge","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/lf-edge/ekuiper","primary":true}]},{"category":"Wasm","homepage_url":"https://www.envoyproxy.io","id":"wasm--embedded-functions--envoy-wasm","logo":"logos/1cb1ec893e39b60f7d14dc76c6cc1e597b24be0161c0bdf9f97442fcb8d331f9.svg","name":"Envoy (Wasm)","subcategory":"Embedded Functions","website":"https://www.envoyproxy.io","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy","primary":true}]},{"category":"Wasm","homepage_url":"https://www.fluvio.io/","id":"wasm--embedded-functions--infinyon","logo":"logos/d122343ab68ce256f67f3983e07f641c810af212047b3e65a237cff0fde29aac.svg","name":"Infinyon","subcategory":"Embedded Functions","website":"https://www.fluvio.io/","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/infinyon","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/infinyon/fluvio","primary":true}]},{"category":"Wasm","homepage_url":"https://istio.io/","id":"wasm--embedded-functions--istio-wasm","logo":"logos/2d881599f6faed0a16840a675049bd10ce7096134d93df3f533aaf91972a9689.svg","name":"Istio (Wasm)","subcategory":"Embedded Functions","website":"https://istio.io/","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","description":"Simplify observability, traffic management, security, and policy with the Istio service mesh.","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/istio/istio","primary":tr